setup:
You're refactoring old code and find this function:

```js
const calculate = function(items) {
  let total = 0;
  for (let item of items) {
    total += item.price * item.quantity;
  }
  return total;
};
```

A colleague suggests converting it to an arrow function for consistency with the rest of the codebase.

A junior developer writes this code and is confused about why `double(5)` returns undefined:

```js
const double = (n) => {
  n * 2;
};

console.log(double(5)); // undefined
```
